 <title>WBU-16-0008 - In the Matter of Jim Kapsales	</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/oha/downloads/wbu-16-0008-matter-jim-kapsales</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;/oha/downloads/wbu-16-0008-matter-jim-kapsales&quot; class=&quot;title-link&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;WBU-16-0008 - In the Matter of Jim Kapsales	&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;On November 17, 2016, OHA denied an Appeal of a dismissal of a Complaint filed by Mr. Jim Kapsales against Lawrence Livermore National Lab (LLNL) under DOE’s Contractor Employee Protection Program, 10 CFR Part 708.  In his Complaint, Mr. Kapsales alleged that he made two protected disclosures concerning a Government Accountability Office (GAO) audit questionnaire and a GAO proposed agenda.  He further alleged that LLNL abused its authority in interfering with his attempts to respond to government requests for information and that, in retaliation for these alleged disclosures, LLNL instructed its subcontractor, M.H. Chew, to terminate its subcontract with Mr. Kapsales.  In dismissing the complaint, the National Nuclear Security Administration (NNSA) concluded that Mr. Kapsales had not alleged any facts upon which relief could be granted.  On Appeal, OHA found, considering all arguments and supporting evidence in a light most favorable to Mr. Kapsales, that dismissal was appropriate.  Accordingly, OHA denied the Appeal.&lt;/p&gt;
