<item>
 <title>WBA-15-0009 - In the Matter of Sandra Black</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/oha/downloads/wba-15-0009-matter-sandra-black</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;/oha/downloads/wba-15-0009-matter-sandra-black&quot; class=&quot;title-link&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;WBA-15-0009 - In the Matter of Sandra Black&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;On December 31, 2015, OHA denied an Appeal involving a Complaint filed by Sandra Black against Savannah River Nuclear Solutions, LLC (SRNS) under the DOE’s Contractor Employee Protection Program, 10 CFR Part 708. In her Complaint, Black alleged SRNS terminated her for engaging in protected activities, specifically citing her participation in a Government Accountability Office review as a protected disclosure. An OHA Attorney-Investigator dismissed Black’s Complaint because she also filed a whistleblower complaint with the U.S. Department of Labor based on “the same facts” as alleged in the Part 708 complaint. On review, OHA affirmed the finding of the OHA Attorney-Investigator that OHA lacked jurisdiction over Black’s complaint pursuant to 10 CFR §§ 708.15(c), (d) and 708.17(c)(3). Consequently, OHA denied Black’s Appeal. &lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-download-files field-type-file field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;media-link-wrapper&quot; href=&quot;https://energy.gov/sites/prod/files/2016/01/f28/WBA-15-0009.pdf&quot;&gt;&lt;img typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; src=&quot;/modules/file/icons/application-pdf.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;filename&quot;&gt;WBA-15-0009.pdf&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;filesize&quot;&gt;(106.73 KB)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
